---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../config/site";

const lastUpdated = "May 24, 2026";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description={`Terms and conditions for using ${site.name}.`}
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
>
  <p>
    These Terms of Service (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your access to and use of <strong>{site.name}</strong>
    software, APIs, website, and related services (collectively, the &ldquo;Service&rdquo;). By using the
    Service, you agree to these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
  <p>
    You must be at least 13 years old (or the age required in your country) and able to form a binding
    contract. If you use the Service on behalf of an organization, you represent that you have authority to
    bind that organization.
  </p>

  <h2>2. The Service</h2>
  <p>
    JARVIS interprets natural language, produces structured plans, and can execute tasks on computers and
    devices you configure. Features vary by platform and release; we may change, suspend, or discontinue
    features with reasonable notice where practicable.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Service is provided on an evolving basis during active development. It is not guaranteed to be
    error-free or available at all times.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Your account and security</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for safeguarding credentials, OAuth authorizations, and devices paired to your
    account. Notify us promptly at <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a> if you
    suspect unauthorized access.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the Service for unlawful, harmful, or fraudulent purposes.</li>
    <li>Attempt to access systems, accounts, or data without authorization.</li>
    <li>Reverse engineer or circumvent security except where law expressly permits.</li>
    <li>Overload or disrupt the Service or third-party APIs connected through JARVIS.</li>
    <li>Use automation to harm others or to operate devices without the owner&rsquo;s knowledge and consent.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You remain responsible for actions JARVIS performs on your machines after you issue commands or approve
    steps.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    Sign-in and integrations (Google, GitHub, Spotify, YouTube, Classroom, and others) are subject to those
    providers&rsquo; terms and policies. We are not responsible for third-party services.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    We retain rights in the Service, branding, and documentation. Open-source components are licensed under
    their respective licenses. You retain rights in content you provide; you grant us a limited license to
    process that content solely to operate and improve the Service for you.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> explains how we handle personal data and is incorporated into
    these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
  <p>
    THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED &ldquo;AS IS&rdquo; AND &ldquo;AS AVAILABLE&rdquo; WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND,
    WHETHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND
    NON-INFRINGEMENT. JARVIS MAY MISUNDERSTAND REQUESTS OR EXECUTE INCORRECT ACTIONS; REVIEW IMPORTANT
    OUTCOMES BEFORE RELYING ON THEM.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, WE AND OUR CONTRIBUTORS WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR INDIRECT,
    INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR FOR LOSS OF DATA, PROFITS, OR GOODWILL,
    ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE. OUR TOTAL LIABILITY FOR ANY CLAIM RELATING TO THE SERVICE IS
    LIMITED TO THE GREATER OF (A) AMOUNTS YOU PAID US IN THE TWELVE MONTHS BEFORE THE CLAIM OR (B) ONE
    HUNDRED U.S. DOLLARS (USD $100), EXCEPT WHERE LIABILITY CANNOT BE LIMITED BY LAW.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
  <p>
    You will defend and indemnify us against claims arising from your misuse of the Service, violation of
    these Terms, or infringement of third-party rights, to the extent permitted by law.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You may stop using the Service at any time. We may suspend or terminate access if you breach these Terms
    or if required for security or legal reasons. Provisions that by nature should survive (disclaimers,
    liability limits, indemnity) survive termination.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction where the operator of JARVIS is established,
    without regard to conflict-of-law rules, except where mandatory consumer protections in your country
    apply. Disputes should first be raised with <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may modify these Terms. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date reflects the current version. Continued
    use after changes constitutes acceptance where permitted by law.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these Terms: <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
